<doc id="1031981" wikidata="Q1649813" url="?curid=1031981" title="Espírito Santo do Pinhal">
<text>Espírito Santo do Pinhal (Portuguese meaning &quot;Holy Spirit of Pinhal&quot;) is a municipality in the state of São Paulo in Brazil. The population in 2020 is 44,471 (IBGE 2020) and the area is 389 km2. The elevation is 870 m.

== Media ==
In telecommunications, the city was served by Telecomunicações de São Paulo. In July 1998, this company was acquired by Telefónica, which adopted the Vivo brand in 2012. The company is currently an operator of cell phones, fixed lines, internet (fiber optics/4G) and television (satellite and cable).

==Notable people==
*Sebastião da Silveira Cintra
